President Biden delivered a speech in Kansas City, Missouri, highlighting the importance of the recently passed infrastructure law and his Build Back Better plan. He paid tribute to Bob Dole, a former senator from Kansas who recently passed away, and praised his leadership and service. The President emphasized the need to invest in America's infrastructure, including roads, bridges, ports, and airports, to create jobs and improve the country's competitiveness. He also discussed the importance of affordable childcare, universal pre-K, lower prescription drug prices, and access to high-speed internet. President Biden outlined his plan to pay for these investments by asking corporations and the wealthiest Americans to pay their fair share of taxes. He concluded by expressing his belief that America can win the competition for the 21st century and create a better future for all.